//*****************************************************SQL SETUP Inside DOcker*********************************//

Steps to setup SQL server in Docker : 

1. Install Docker 

	sudo apt-get -y install docker-ce
	sudo usermod -aG docker ${USER}

//at this stage Logout from your macine and Login back, to make your user as admin user for docker 

2. Install Docker-Compose

	//Replace username in below command
 sudo curl -L https://github.com/docker/compose/releases/download/1.18.0/docker-compose-`uname -s`-`uname -m` -o /usr/local/bin/docker-compose

3. Go to src folder
4. run : "docker-compose up -d" . 
5. This will start the SQL container.
6. Loging to the container using : 'docker exec -it "container-name" bash'

7. Once inside container : 
		run below commands
			a. mysql -u root -p pass
			b.  if it again prompts for password , then type "pass"

8. Now once inside mysql , you can tun queries. 

		1. use IceCreamsDB;
		2. CREATE TABLE IceCreams
	( Name varchar(50) NOT NULL,
	  ImageClosed Text ,
	  ImageOpen Text ,
	  Description Text ,
	  Story Text ,
	  SourcingValues Text ,
	  Ingredients Text ,
	  AllergyInfo Text ,
	  DietaryCertifications Text ,
	  ProductID varchar(50) NOT NULL
	);



//****************************THIS COMPLETES YOUR SQL SETUP INSIDE DOCKER****************************//


